<br>
Say you wanted to show the character in 4 views, front, back, side, and 3/4ths-<br>
<br>
Would there be a good &quot;just standing there&quot; pose that I can use for character designs, so I can show the character in that one pose for all of those views?<br>
<br>
Its hard to explain what I'm trying to say- Like say you introduced your boss with a sheet of paper showing your new character from several views so he/she can get the feel for how it's going to look<br>
<br>
I don't want to draw them just standing up perfectly straight, because that's just bland <p><a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/bmilitaryandpolitics>Visit my Military, History, and Politics BBS</a>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulinabo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LinaBo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>PK Angel</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 12:03:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4419.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.marua.com/ifk/avatars/Linapic.jpg width=100 height=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Character design</span><hr size=1> okay, so let me get this straight... you want to draw them 'just standing there', but you don't want to draw them 'just standing up perfectly straight', because it's boring? Do you realize that you're kind of contradicting yourself?<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think the key thing you're looking for is to have the face and torso facing either front, back, or either side. Fom there, experiment with slight variations on placement of arms/legs etc. Incorporate 'props' like guns etc, if the character carries one. Demonstrate personality traits through gestures and expressions. Try to draw your character relaxed, because no one actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> poses</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in a tense position. That's for action shots. <p>'I'll try being nicer if you try being smarter'</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uburncycle360.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Burncycle360</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 8:00:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4419.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Character design</span><hr size=1> I said it was hard to explain what I ment -_- <p><a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/bmilitaryandpolitics>Visit my Military, History, and Politics BBS</a>

